History.Recent History:
Following the [[Godswar]] of 1358 DR, with her waxing faith, theologians of the 1360s DR predicted Selûne would once again be elevated among the gods, possibly within their own lifetimes.

In the aftermath of the Time of Troubles, the clergy grew in strength. To atone for being tricked by Shar, Naneatha launched a crusade against Shar's followers and drove them out of the city by [[1372 DR]]. Naneatha also firmly supported the establishment of the [[Order of the Blue Moon]], dedicated to both Selûne and [[Mystra (Midnight)|Mystra]].

After the [[Spellplague]] happened in the [[1385 DR|Year of Blue Fire, 1385 DR]], Selûne became a popular deity across Faerûn, as her priesthood made pilgrimages to every corner of the continent, wanting to bring hope to people in those desperate times.{{Cite dungeon/193/Shards of Selûne|21}}
